:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3,\"repo\":\"thompsonemerson/bower-files-cli\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Get main bower files on the command line.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:54:16.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Cross-platform Shell Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Use <code>&#x26;&#x26;</code> to run commands in sequence. If a command fails, the script exits.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:54:16.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Cross-platform Shell Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Use <code>|</code> to pipe the stdout of one command into the stdin of the next. (<code>do-something | something else</code>)</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:54:16.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Cross-platform Shell Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Use <code>></code> to write the stdout of a command to a file. (<code>do-something > file</code>)</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:54:16.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Cross-platform Shell Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Use <code>&#x3C;</code> to send the contents of a file to a command's stdin. (<code>command &#x3C; file</code>)</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:54:16.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Cross-platform Shell Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Use <code>cd &#x3C;dir></code> to change the current working directory to <code>&#x3C;dir></code>. Note that <code>cd</code> alone prints the current working directory on windows, but changes the working directory to <code>~</code> on *nix.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:54:16.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Miscellaneous</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/