er-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":4,\"repo\":\"iamakulov/echo-cli\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Cross-platform <code>echo</code> with JS escape sequence support.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-09-07T20:00:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Utilities</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/keithamus/hashmark\">hashmark</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/keithamus/hashmark\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">194</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":194,\"repo\":\"keithamus/hashmark\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> -  Take contents of a file and output as new file with a hash in the name.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-09-07T20:00:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2><code>npm run</code> Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Run just <code>npm run</code> to print a list of scripts.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-09-07T20:00:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2><code>npm run</code> Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Running <code>npm run script</code> (where <code>script</code> is the name of your script) will run <code>prescript</code>, <code>script</code>, and <code>postscript</code>; in that order.\n<ul>\n<li>You can't nest <code>pre</code> and <code>post</code> hooks (i.e. <code>preprescript</code> won't work).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-09-07T20:00:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2><code>npm run</code> Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Running <code>npm test</code> is the same as running <code>npm run test</code>. The same applies to <code>npm start</code> and <code>npm stop</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-09-07T20:00:06.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/sindresorhus/awesome-observables","repo":"sindresorhus/awesome-observables"},"next":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/Richienb/awesome-ponyfills","repo":"Richienb/awesome-ponyfills"}},"pageContext":{"type":"week","repo":"RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts","id":"awesomes/github.com/RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/sindresorhus/awesome-observables","nextId":"awesomes/github.com/Richienb/awesome-ponyfills"}},"staticQueryHashes":["147714651","228695001","2744905544"]}